The paper discusses indexing structures for strings and tries, which are fundamental data structures in computer science. The focus is on suffix trees, DAWGs, and CDAWGs, which are commonly used in bioinformatics, information retrieval, and data mining. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the size and space complexity of these structures, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions information retrieval and data mining, which are subfields of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DM (Data Mining), respectively.
